; VTA bulge-shaped; RTA straight, stiletto-shape, directed anteriad; the cymbium with a well-developed cymbial lateral process; the tegulum small, poorly marked, without a visible tegular process; the functional tegulum narrow-elongated, with well-developed, wide and obtuse proximal projection (PP) and with a long, cone-shaped distal projection (DP); the embolus long, small swordshaped, with a wide round base.
